+Review the git diff and fix issues or log them as skipped.
+
+TARGET DIFF:
+Default: master~6..HEAD (covers the 6 v3 worker merges)
+Override via env var REVIEW_TARGET if needed.
+
+ISSUE CATEGORIES (defined in your Custom Mode rules):
+- Security: SQL injection, XSS, missing auth, secret leaks
+- Performance: N+1 queries, missing indexes, sync I/O in hot paths
+- Error handling: missing try/catch, swallowed errors, no resource cleanup
+- Code smells: dead code, unclear names, magic numbers
+
+DECISION LOGIC:
+For each issue found, choose one:
+  SIMPLE FIX: Small, local, low-risk change
+    ÔåÆ Commit with prefix "fix: " and clear message
+    ÔåÆ Example: "fix: add try/catch to db.connect in server.js"
+  
+  COMPLEX: Cross-cutting, refactor needed, or ambiguous
+    ÔåÆ Log as skipped with one-line reason
+    ÔåÆ Example: "Skipped: N+1 in /api/workers needs query redesign"
+
+When in doubt, skip and log. Aggressive skipping is preferred over risky fixes.
+
+OUTPUT FILES:
+1. .foreman/tasks/reviewer.json
+   Schema: See V3-PLAN.md (run_id, summary{issues_found, auto_fixed, skipped}, interventions[])
+   
+2. .foreman/reviewer-history.json
+   Read existing if present, increment lifetime totals, append this run to runs[]
+   Schema: See V3-PLAN.md (lifetime{total_runs, total_issues_found, total_auto_fixed, total_skipped}, runs[])
+
+NEVER TOUCH:
+- .foreman-prompts/* (sacred, no recursion)
+- V3-PLAN.md
+- scripts/foreman-review.ps1
+- .foreman-prompts/reviewer.txt (this file)
+- LICENSE, README.md, CHANGELOG.md
+
+STDOUT:
+Print exactly one line when done:
+Reviewer done: N found, M fixed, K skipped
+
+WORKFLOW:
+1. Read diff (git diff master~6..HEAD or $env:REVIEW_TARGET)
+2. For each hunk, evaluate against issue categories
+3. Fix or skip each issue
+4. Write .foreman/tasks/reviewer.json
+5. Update .foreman/reviewer-history.json
+6. Print summary line

